parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of metal brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to loss of brake function, which can result in accidents or injuries.
Inadequate braking performance can cause accidents or injuries, especially in panic stop situations.
symptoms: feeling of only rear wheels braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden loss of brake function can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal and Gas Pedal Design
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor design of brake and gas pedals can cause unintended acceleration or braking, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the ABS system can cause loss of brake function, leading to accidents or injuries.

premature replacement of rear brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped or overheated brake rotors can cause loss of brake function, leading to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries or fatalities.
